I know nothing about football (I know which teams are playing and when the game is but had to look up which team is AFC and which is NFC - just to demonstrate how little I know), so my prediction is based solely on my friend's allegiance (which is based on a personal connection to a team member). There's no scientific rationale or basis to my prediction and I have no idea how to even begin to assess strengths and weaknesses of each team, and then there's always a chance that a seemingly improbable result will occur - one perfect pass, one injury, one bad call, these can all change the outcome in a moment.

PHI enters the game with the best defense in the NFL and has decisively knocked off SF (second-best Defense) in the NFC title game, 30-7. KC extremely beats up with a QB recovering from a high ankle sprain TE with back injuries suffered before the AFC title match and a receiving corps riddled with injuries. KC enters the contest with the most (recent) postseason and SB experience of the two teams. However, KC's defense is extremely vulnerable to the run...with two quality running back and a host of receiving weapons, PHI is in a position to come away with the win.

AFC (Eagles) vs NFC (Chiefs) - AFC won 27 of 24 matches. Lots of streaks - so hard to use this data. Chiefs and Eagles have met 9 times. Chiefs win 5 / Eagles win 4. Again, nearly split. Lots of injuries on the Chiefs. Eagles are healthy - but two weeks until the game (as of Jan 30). Weighted to Chiefs due to overall team stats (yards, pts per game, etc.)
Too many injuries for the Chiefs

My above forecast is based on injury report from the conference championship this past weekend. The Eagles are coming into the super bowl completely healthy, while the Chiefs are pretty banged up. The Chiefs star quarterback Patrick Mahomes is suffering from a high sprain ankle injury that clearly affected him during the conference championship game against the Bengals. As well as standout tight end Travis Kelce suffering from a low back injury. I believe that the Eagles defense is going to cause a lot of issue for the offensive of the Chiefs, not allowing Patrick Mahomes the time needed to make the play he normally can make. The Eagles also have the best defensive line and secondary in the league. Which will make it extremely difficult on the Chiefs to keep up with the high scoring, high pace offense of the Eagles.
